<subSubSection id="C358655E860E6B28FD838B89FE0CF64D" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860E6B28FD838B89FCF2F7BF" blockId="28.[603,872,2045,2084]" box="[603,872,2045,2084]" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">
<heading id="D0B581B9860E6B28FD838B89FCF2F7BF" box="[603,872,2045,2084]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" reason="3">PI. 20 figs 1-7</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860E6B28FEF0841AFE0CF64D" blockId="28.[247,1230,2158,2518]" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">Description. Shell minute, thin, globose, rather short spired, narrowly phaneromphalous. Protoconch of 114 smooth whorls, apex deviated, between protoconch and teleoconch sharp straight line; teleoconch of 3-4 very convex whorls, with surface smooth except for very distinct opisthocline growth lines, suture deep. Aperture simple, complete circular, lips thin.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
