<subSubSection id="C358655E860E6B28FA9E8E54FAF4FCB7" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860E6B28FA9E8E54FAF4FCB7" blockId="28.[1303,2283,442,812]" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860E6B28F9DA8E54F888FDDD" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1538,1810,544,582]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="globosa" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860E6B28F9DA8E54F888FDDD" box="[1538,1810,544,582]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">Kimina globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860E6B28F8FA8E54F8F7FDDD" box="[1826,1901,544,582]" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860E6B28F8118E54F773FDDD" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1993,2281,544,582]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="australis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860E6B28F8118E54F773FDDD" box="[1993,2281,544,582]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">Kimina australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860E6B28FACF8E39FAF9FDEF" box="[1303,1379,589,628]" pageId="28" pageNumber="91" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar in having a smooth shell with a deviated protoconch and moderate umbilicus, but different each other in that the former has opisthocline growth lines, while the latter has prosocline growth lines.
</paragraph>
